At this time the length of night and the shortness of day reach to their extremes once again, and the day begins to grow longer than the night. Autumn is finished, winter has arrived. Cold is intense, bitter winds b10w‚ the leaves of the trees fall, most of the vegetation dies, and most of the animals take refuge in the belly of the earth and in mountain caves from the severe cold and the frequent storms and rain. The heavens grow dark and the face of the earth frowns. The animals grow thin, bodies grow weaker‚ and the world becomes like a decrepit old woman to whom death draws near.
